            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Judges.17:1-18:31",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJudges%2017%3A1-18%3A31%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_1%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJudges%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EMicah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Idols%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20was%20a%20man%20named%20Micah%2C%20who%20lived%20in%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Ephraim.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_2%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20he%20said%20to%20his%20mother%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20heard%20you%20place%20a%20curse%20on%20the%20person%20who%20stole%201%2C100%20pieces%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E17%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E1%2C100%20%5Bshekels%5D%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%2028%26%23xA0%3Bpounds%20or%2012.5%26%23xA0%3Bkilograms%20in%20weight.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20silver%20from%20you.%20Well%2C%20I%20have%20the%20money.%20I%20was%20the%20one%20who%20took%20it.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20bless%20you%20for%20admitting%20it%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20his%20mother%20replied.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_3%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20returned%20the%20money%20to%20her%2C%20and%20she%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20now%20dedicate%20these%20silver%20coins%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20In%20honor%20of%20my%20son%2C%20I%20will%20have%20an%20image%20carved%20and%20an%20idol%20cast.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_4%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20when%20he%20returned%20the%20money%20to%20his%20mother%2C%20she%20took%20200%26%23xA0%3Bsilver%20coins%20and%20gave%20them%20to%20a%20silversmith%2C%20who%20made%20them%20into%20an%20image%20and%20an%20idol.%20And%20these%20were%20placed%20in%20Micah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_5%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EMicah%20set%20up%20a%20shrine%20for%20the%20idol%2C%20and%20he%20made%20a%20sacred%20ephod%20and%20some%20household%20idols.%20Then%20he%20installed%20one%20of%20his%20sons%20as%20his%20personal%20priest.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_6%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20those%20days%20Israel%20had%20no%20king%3B%20all%20the%20people%20did%20whatever%20seemed%20right%20in%20their%20own%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_7%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20a%20young%20Levite%2C%20who%20had%20been%20living%20in%20Bethlehem%20in%20Judah%2C%20arrived%20in%20that%20area.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_8%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20had%20left%20Bethlehem%20in%20search%20of%20another%20place%20to%20live%2C%20and%20as%20he%20traveled%2C%20he%20came%20to%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Ephraim.%20He%20happened%20to%20stop%20at%20Micah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house%20as%20he%20was%20traveling%20through.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_9%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhere%20are%20you%20from%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Micah%20asked%20him.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EHe%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20a%20Levite%20from%20Bethlehem%20in%20Judah%2C%20and%20I%20am%20looking%20for%20a%20place%20to%20live.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_10%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BStay%20here%20with%20me%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Micah%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Band%20you%20can%20be%20a%20father%20and%20priest%20to%20me.%20I%20will%20give%20you%20ten%20pieces%20of%20silver%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E17%3A10%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E10%26%23xA0%3B%5Bshekels%5D%20of%20silver%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%204%26%23xA0%3Bounces%20or%20114%26%23xA0%3Bgrams%20in%20weight.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20a%20year%2C%20plus%20a%20change%20of%20clothes%20and%20your%20food.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_11%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Levite%20agreed%20to%20this%2C%20and%20the%20young%20man%20became%20like%20one%20of%20Micah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sons.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_12%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Micah%20installed%20the%20Levite%20as%20his%20personal%20priest%2C%20and%20he%20lived%20in%20Micah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_17_13%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20know%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20bless%20me%20now%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Micah%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bbecause%20I%20have%20a%20Levite%20serving%20as%20my%20priest.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_18_1%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJudges%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EIdolatry%20in%20the%20Tribe%20of%20Dan%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20in%20those%20days%20Israel%20had%20no%20king.%20And%20the%20tribe%20of%20Dan%20was%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20place%20where%20they%20could%20settle%2C%20for%20they%20had%20not%20yet%20moved%20into%20the%20land%20assigned%20to%20them%20when%20the%20land%20was%20divided%20among%20the%20tribes%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_18_2%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20men%20of%20Dan%20chose%20from%20their%20clans%20five%20capable%20warriors%20from%20the%20towns%20of%20Zorah%20and%20Eshtaol%20to%20scout%20out%20a%20land%20for%20them%20to%20settle%20in.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EWhen%20these%20warriors%20arrived%20in%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Ephraim%2C%20they%20came%20to%20Micah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house%20and%20spent%20the%20night%20there.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_18_3%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EWhile%20at%20Micah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house%2C%20they%20recognized%20the%20young%20Levite%26%23x2019%3Bs%20accent%2C%20so%20they%20went%20over%20and%20asked%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWho%20brought%20you%20here%2C%20and%20what%20are%20you%20doing%20in%20this%20place%3F%20Why%20ar